Former PIC CEO Dan Matjila took the hot seat at the PIC inquiry on Monday. Police Minister Bheki Cele is in Philippi East in the Western Cape after a 72-hour action plan was put in place. The Pretoria man accused of the attempted murder of a homeless man won't have a fair trial, according to his family. Manusi Mothupi's brother Oupa spoke to eNCA about his fears. For 17 years, Khululekile Moko has been collecting waste and recyclables to put food on the table for his family. Good Samaritan Kevin Kinwelle has built him a new ride that will make the daily grind so much better. Former Chief of State Protocol, Ambassador Bruce Koloane, testified at the state capture inquiry on Monday.